    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect bit field extraction in EPS Network Feature Support IE\n\n### Summary\nThe EPS Network Feature Support information element decoder only extracted a single bit (IMS VoPS) instead of the complete set of network feature flags. This caused incomplete debug output in NAS tracing and potentially incorrect network behavior negotiation.\n\nThe issue was introduced when the IE structure was simplified from a proper bit field to a single uint8_t, losing the multi-bit interpretation required by 3GPP TS 24.301.\n\nUnder network conditions where extended EPS features are negotiated, this leads to:\n- Incomplete XML debug traces missing EMC BS, EPC LS, and other feature flags\n- Potential misinterpretation of network capabilities during attach procedures\n- Segfault when accessing uninitialized bit fields in debug mode\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsNetworkFeatureSupport.h`: Restored proper bit field structure for all 6 defined EPS features\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsNetworkFeatureSupport.c`: Fixed decode/encode functions to handle complete bit field extraction\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsNetworkFeatureSupport.c`: Enhanced dump function to show all feature flags individually\n\nTo reproduce: Enable NAS debug tracing and initiate an attach procedure with a network advertising extended EPS features. Observe that only the IMS VoPS flag appears in traces, and other flags like EMC BS are missing even when present in the air interface capture.\n"
}